cinating detail. Arab Seafaring will appeal to anyone interested in Arab life or the history of navigation. For this expanded edition, John Carswell has added a new introduction, a bibliography, and notes that add material from recent archaeological research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aCommercexHistoryyMedieval, 500-1500. 0aCommercexHistoryyTo 500. 0aNavigationzArab countriesxHistory. 0aTrade routeszIndian OceanxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh  aAela.  aArrian.  aBegram.  aBombay.  aCalicut.  aChaldaea.  aChina.  aCoromandel.  aDamascus.  aDilmun.  aEgypt.  aEuphrates River.  aFrankincense.  aGujarat.  aHellenistic.  aHurmuz.  aIndia.  aIndonesia.  aJava.  aKalah Bār.  aKoran.  aKārūn River.  aLaccadive Islands.  aLamu.  aLeuce Come.  aMadagascar.  aMalabar.  aMaldive Islands.  aMozambique.  aNerbudda River.  aOcelis.  aParthia.  aPersian Gulf.  aPliny the Elder.  aPtolemy Claudius.  aRed Sea.  aSassanid.  aSeleucid.  aStrabo.  aTigris River.  aVasco da Gama.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Gap Yearsz978311078423740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691214894?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691214894423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691214894/original  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  a978-3-11-078423-7  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Gap Years  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-a